data.description:
Refined living in a tree-lined tranquil block. Welcome home to 575 East 28th Street. This immaculate mint condition two-family home is now available for sale. *Incredible opportunity to assume the sellers existing mortgage at an interest rate of 3.375%!*  Please contact us for more information on assuming the sellers existing mortgage and interest rate.
This extraordinary home has been tastefully gut renovated with impeccable finishings, overreaching loft like ceilings throughout, a central heating and cooling system, open custom kitchen Carrera marble backsplashes in both units with full stainless-steel appliances, a surround sound system, and many more key premium qualities. The garden level is an owners duplex dream; a floor-through massive layout with three full bathrooms + an expansive lower level with great potential as a work from home set up and additional recreational space! The second-floor residence includes a windowed home office, a separate laundry room â€“ ideal for income generating or as a guest residence. The delightful outdoor space optimizes the allure with a large, amazing rear patio leading to the spacious beautifully maintained backyard filled with magnificent trees. Whats more you can completely re-imagine this home as a single-family triplex or an investment property, as the carrying costs are competitively low. The possibilities are endless! The top floor unit includes sky lights, which is inviting with high ceilings over 10ft.
Conveniently situated in the heart of Brooklyn within proximity to local eateries, cafes, markets, Prospect Park, Brooklyn College, 2/5 Express Trains, shopping centers, highways, and many other amenities Flatbush has to offer.
18 ft X 50 ft building size
18 ft X 100 ft lot size
6 Bedrooms 4 Bathrooms

2,800 Interior Living Space
Current Annual Property Tax: $4,851
Please contact us now for more information on this incredible opportunity. Full set up and property details will be given upon request. Showing by appointment only. Please note: the photos are virtually staged.
